<h1 id=3D"SIEMIntegration-Usecases-Summary">Summary</h1>
<p>As part of the requirement to detect, alert, analyse and respond to thre=
ats on the data within BDP4, Security, information and event management (SI=
EM) will be a solution to satisfy this requirement. SIEM technology collect=
s event log data from a range of sources, identifies activity that deviates=
 from the norm with real-time analysis, and takes appropriate action.</p>
<p>For further context on SIEM, please refer to the following link on the i=
ntegration between SIEM and BDP4 - <a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/HDP/pages/291523=
7955/SIEM+Integration+-+High+level+design" data-linked-resource-id=3D"29152=
37955" data-linked-resource-version=3D"6" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page=
">SIEM Integration - High level design</a> . </p>
<p>The purpose of this document will be to outline the specific use cases f=
or SIEM so that it can be implemented as part of robust alerting and monito=
ring practices within BDP4.</p>
<h1 id=3D"SIEMIntegration-Usecases-Usecases&amp;logsrequiredtoperformusecas=
e">Use cases &amp; logs required to perform use case</h1>
<p>Outlined below are the use cases for SIEM across four categories: <stron=
g>Collect, Correlate, Identify &amp; Alert</strong>. </p>
<p>This list of use cases is expected to grow over time, however, due to th=
e need for an interim solution to be in place for the Program=E2=80=99s goa=
l to deliver priority reports to the business by end Q1 2023, a set of MVP =
use cases have been agreed upon and will be the focus of current effort. Su=
bsequent use cases will be prioritised as needed with agreement by security=
, SIEM SMEs and the Data Program PMs. </p>
<p>Note, Sentinel currently has logs enabled for the following services:</p=
>
<ul>
<li><p><strong>AAD </strong></p></li>
<li><p><strong>Defender for identity </strong></p></li>
<li><p><strong>Cyberarc and Sailpoint for IAM -</strong> For RBAC - onboard=
 system onto Sailpoint for RBAC, access provisioning and ongoing access rev=
iews </p></li>
</ul>
